  "instructions": [
    "In a large bowl, combine the rinsed black beans with tahini, lemon juice, olive oil, red onion, garlic, and salt and pepper. Mix well.",
    "Transfer the mixture into a skillet over medium heat. Cook for about 10 minutes until everything is heated through and flavors are melded together.",
    "Stir in chopped almonds just before serving to keep them from getting too toasted.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish or on its own with pita bread."
